1
00:00:06,133 --> 00:00:07,233
<i> Ash? Xander?</i>

2
00:00:07,367 --> 00:00:09,500
<i>Don't you know I told
Xander to stay away?</i>

3
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:11,100
<i>And you're the one
who brought him there?</i>

4
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:12,567
<i>Did you know Jasmine
had a seizure?</i>

5
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:13,600
<i> Hey, Marj!</i>

6
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:15,033
<i>What are you doing
to my daughter, huh?</i>

7
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:19,467
<i>Next time you go after my kid,
I won't hesitate to hurt you.</i>

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,400
<i>You booked a flight
to Hong Kong?</i>

9
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:23,167
<i>The meds aren't working on her.</i>

10
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,800
<i>I'm not agreeing to your plans!</i>

11
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:27,767
<i>No one can stop me
from curing my daughter!</i>

12
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,967
<i>You convinced my wife
to go to Hong Kong!</i>

13
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:30,933
<i> Are you doing this on purpose?</i>

14
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:32,333
<i>Are you doing this to spite me?</i>

15
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:33,933
<i> You never do anything right!</i>

16
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:35,200
<i>Is that really how
low you think of me?</i>

17
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:37,633
<i> That's how everyone sees you.</i>

18
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:38,700
<i> Even Marj.</i>

19
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,700
<i>That's why she didn't
choose you, right?</i>

20
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:42,367
<i>You want me to go
against my own brother?</i>

21
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,400
<i> If you help me beat him,</i>

22
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:47,133
<i>wouldn't that be your revenge,
too?</i>

23
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:54,433
I expected my daughter's
condition to improve,

24
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:57,567
just like the other patients
on this treatment.

25
00:00:57,700 --> 00:00:59,800
But why is it like this?

26
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:01,467
Why is she getting weaker?

27
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:06,200
Why isn't the pain going away?

28
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:09,633
Several of our patients
also needed time to adjust

29
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,667
because of the extreme pain.

30
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,633
Just hang in there
a little longer.

31
00:01:14,767 --> 00:01:17,767
My team and I are expecting
good results.

32
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:20,467
- Thank you.
- Excuse me,

33
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,400
I need to do my rounds.

34
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:37,567
Am I still doing
the right thing?

35
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:44,967
I'm the reason your suffering
is lasting longer, sweetheart.

36
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,833
I thought I was fighting
for you.

37
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:00,333
I thought I was choosing
what was best for you.

38
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:05,233
But maybe I'm the one
causing you pain.

39
00:02:06,733 --> 00:02:08,533
I made the wrong decision.

40
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,433
I'll never forgive myself.

41
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,533
How do you like it so far?

42
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:08,233
Please feel free to look around.

43
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:09,733
-Okay.
-Orly, take care of them

44
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:11,433
- for now.
- Okay. Thank you.

45
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:12,500
Thank you.

46
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,967
Paolo.

47
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,633
I know you're having
a hard time.

48
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:32,967
But for what it's worth,

49
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:35,667
I don't think Marj has bad
intentions for your child.

50
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:38,433
Jasmine should be okay with her.

51
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:43,600
But right now we're at work.

52
00:03:44,367 --> 00:03:47,533
Forget about Marj and the fact
that she disobeyed you.

53
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:50,267
You don't understand

54
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,067
because you're not
in my position.

55
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,200
Maybe not.

56
00:03:56,967 --> 00:03:58,900
But I'm sure about one thing.

57
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:05,000
Things will only get worse
if you let Aldrin beat you.

58
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,333
Is that what you want?

59
00:04:08,367 --> 00:04:09,200
Of course not.

60
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:11,500
I will never let that happen.

61
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,867
You've been taking that
for a week now, Manang.

62
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,933
Has your eye improved?

63
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:42,033
Nothing happens.

64
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:45,500
My eye just stings from putting
that oil on every night.

65
00:04:45,633 --> 00:04:48,267
And she told me to drink
this three times a day,

66
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,967
but nothing's happening.

67
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:52,300
You should go back
to that faith healer.

68
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:54,533
Yes, Manang Yolly.

69
00:04:54,667 --> 00:04:55,867
So you can get your money back.

70
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,600
Wasn't that the promise?

71
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:59,000
Yes.

72
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:01,100
She said she'd return it
if it didn't work.

73
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:02,133
That should be.

74
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:06,233
Manang Yolly, do you want us
to go with you?

75
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:09,900
Just to make sure that person
doesn't scam you.

76
00:05:20,267 --> 00:05:21,200
It's going to be okay.

77
00:06:37,633 --> 00:06:38,667
Hey! Be careful!

78
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,767
- What the!
- Sorry.

79
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,533
Oh, my legs!

80
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,167
I'm really sorry.

81
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:45,000
I'm so sorry.

82
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:47,300
What are you even doing here
now?

83
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:49,400
Do we need to fire the guard?

84
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:52,400
They're letting just anyone in.

85
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:56,533
I went to the skate park,
so I decided to drop by.

86
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,000
You do skateboard?

87
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:01,967
There's a lot more you
can learn about me.

88
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:05,033
Just like there's a lot
I still want to know about you.

89
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:06,767
Like, why do you look so sad
today?

90
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:16,067
Nothing.

91
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:18,500
I just miss Jas.

92
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:20,567
I'm worried about her.

93
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:27,533
I read about experimental
leukemia treatments...

94
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:31,067
It got me scared

95
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,267
because they said they're really
painful.

96
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,067
Hey, everything's going to be
okay.

97
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,833
We know Jasmine.

98
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:40,033
Even if she's sick, she's tough.

99
00:07:40,167 --> 00:07:41,533
She's a fighter.

100
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,500
She's not just my best friend.

101
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,300
She's like a sister to me.

102
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:56,900
I just don't want to lose her.

103
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,933
Hey! You're not going
to lose her.

104
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:03,267
Everything's going to be okay.

105
00:08:10,467 --> 00:08:11,700
Manang, I'm sorry!

106
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,633
I'm so sorry!

107
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:14,500
Manang, I'm sorry!

108
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:15,500
I'm so sorry!

109
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:16,833
It's my fault, Manang.

110
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:19,233
- It's all my fault.
- Manang Yolly!

111
00:08:19,367 --> 00:08:20,933
I'm so sorry, Manang.

112
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,133
Manang Yolly, calm down.

113
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:23,867
Our boss might hear you.

114
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,900
What happened?

115
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:29,433
My 100,000 pesos
savings are gone!

116
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:35,533
We went back to Madame Elsa's
house to get the donation back

117
00:08:35,667 --> 00:08:39,733
because the oil she gave me
didn't work.

118
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:41,800
But when we got there,
she was gone.

119
00:08:41,933 --> 00:08:43,833
All her things were gone, too!

120
00:08:43,967 --> 00:08:44,800
Oh, no!

121
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:45,933
See? I told you!

122
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,100
You! You know what?

123
00:08:48,233 --> 00:08:49,400
This is your fault!

124
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:52,267
That faith healer was
obviously a scam!

125
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:55,467
Why did you insist on
taking Manang Yolly there?

126
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:58,433
- It's your fault!
- Okay, fine!

127
00:08:58,567 --> 00:08:59,300
It's my fault!

128
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:00,867
That's why I'm apologizing!

129
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,100
It's my fault!

130
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:03,133
That's enough!

131
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:04,233
Blame me!

132
00:09:04,367 --> 00:09:06,600
It's all my fault!

133
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:08,333
Manang, I'm sorry!

134
00:09:10,367 --> 00:09:12,367
Hey, quit it.

135
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,500
Manang.

136
00:09:13,633 --> 00:09:14,800
Let's find her.

137
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:18,033
She can't just run
away with your money.

138
00:09:18,167 --> 00:09:19,833
How?

139
00:09:19,967 --> 00:09:21,300
Where do we even start?

140
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:22,633
Let's report it
to the police.

141
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:24,933
That money's gone.

142
00:09:25,067 --> 00:09:26,033
It's really gone.

143
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:32,733
Doctor, I'm sorry.

144
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:36,400
When I agreed to the
experimental treatment,

145
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:40,900
I didn't expect my child to go
through something this hard.

146
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:43,467
We've already had several
rounds,

147
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,767
but there's still no change
in her condition.

148
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:49,900
Mrs. Torrecampo,
you have to be patient.

149
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:54,100
We're doing our best
to cure your child.

150
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:03,833
I can't bear watching my child
suffer anymore.

151
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:07,767
I'm sorry, but we won't continue
the treatment.

152
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:12,800
We'll go back to the Philippines
and consider other options.

153
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,667
I respect your decision.

154
00:10:20,167 --> 00:10:22,433
I'll make the necessary
arrangements.

155
00:10:22,567 --> 00:10:23,433
Excuse me.

156
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:31,033
Mom...

157
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:33,733
I'm sorry.

158
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:38,633
I really wanted to get
better for you, but...

159
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:41,333
The pain is just too much.

160
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,667
It's okay. I understand.

161
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,867
And I'm sorry.

162
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,500
I'm so sorry, my child.

163
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,767
I should be the one apologizing.

164
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:53,200
Please forgive me.

165
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:57,300
I shouldn't have forced you
to come here.

166
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:00,400
Your dad was right.

167
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:01,867
I'm so sorry.

168
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:04,267
Let's go home.

169
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,967
Is this going to stop now?

170
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,200
Yes.

171
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,233
Yes, it's going to stop.

172
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,867
I'm taking you home.

173
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:13,833
I'm sorry.

174
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:45,733
Jasmine!

175
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:48,900
- Sorry, Auntie.
- Ma'am Marj.

176
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:51,033
How are you?

177
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:53,500
Are you feeling better?

178
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:55,067
Did the treatment work?

179
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:03,367
Jasmine!

180
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,333
Jasmine, sweetheart!

181
00:12:11,567 --> 00:12:14,700
It's so nice to have you home,
my granddaughter.

182
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:20,100
Jasmine...

183
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:28,500
Oscar, please take Jasmine
to her room.

184
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:29,967
She needs to rest.

185
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:35,500
- Jasmine!
- Jasmine!

186
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:37,933
How are you?

187
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:39,133
I'm glad you're back.

188
00:12:44,433 --> 00:12:45,433
Go ahead.

189
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:54,167
You always think
you know better!

190
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,333
What happened to all
that showing off, huh?

191
00:12:57,467 --> 00:13:00,667
You put my granddaughter's
life in danger!

192
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:06,700
I understand you just wanted
Jasmine to get better.

193
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:11,033
But it was a huge mistake, Marj,

194
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:12,633
to decide everything
on your own.

195
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:16,933
You're not the only one
who wants the best for Jasmine.

196
00:13:18,267 --> 00:13:19,667
We do, too.

197
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,833
Especially Paolo.

198
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:26,867
You didn't just disregard
your husband with what you did.

199
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:31,133
You also disrespected us.

200
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:41,533
I'm sorry I didn't inform
everyone properly.

201
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:47,367
But I never regretted trying.

202
00:13:48,733 --> 00:13:51,667
I wanted to exhaust every option
for Jasmine.

203
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,833
Marj, just apologize.

204
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,333
You already admitted
your mistake.

205
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:01,700
Being proud right now
won't help.

206
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:04,700
Why?

207
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:05,867
If your child were sick,

208
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,067
wouldn't you do the same thing
I did?

209
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,533
Be honest.

210
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:10,833
No pretending.

211
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:15,467
Honestly?

212
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,933
If Ashley were in
Jasmine's position,

213
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:19,867
I would never risk her safety.

214
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:20,900
For what?

215
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:24,633
An experimental treatment
with no guarantee?

216
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:26,533
What are you trying to say?

217
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,067
That I harmed my own child?

218
00:14:29,467 --> 00:14:31,267
- Yes. Why?
- Thea!

219
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,267
That's enough!

220
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,833
Why? It's the truth.

221
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:36,767
You risked Jasmine's life.

222
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:39,133
If anything bad had
happened to her,

223
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:40,833
you would be the only one
to blame!

224
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:52,333
Fine. Blame everything on me.

225
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:55,733
But deep inside, I know I did
the right thing!

226
00:14:55,867 --> 00:14:57,300
That's enough!

227
00:14:57,433 --> 00:14:58,400
Come with me.

228
00:14:58,533 --> 00:14:59,467
Come with me!

229
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,033
Don't grab me like that!

230
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:12,167
I'm really sorry about
what happened in Hong Kong.

231
00:15:13,633 --> 00:15:16,500
There must be other
treatment options.

232
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:21,133
This isn't the end, okay?

233
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:23,567
I can still feel it, Ash.

234
00:15:25,433 --> 00:15:28,167
All those injections
they kept giving me.

235
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:32,100
The burning feeling
from the medicine.

236
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,633
I tried to endure it
as long as I could.

237
00:15:39,033 --> 00:15:41,000
Because I felt so sorry for Mom.

238
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:46,267
I could see how badly she wanted
the treatment to work.

239
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,167
But in the end...

240
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:50,733
I was the one who gave up.

241
00:15:51,933 --> 00:15:53,267
I failed my mom.

242
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,533
I should've been stronger.

243
00:15:57,067 --> 00:15:58,333
I should've fought harder.

244
00:15:58,467 --> 00:15:59,633
Jas...

245
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:01,867
So they wouldn't blame Mom.

246
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:06,100
So they wouldn't be angry
at her anymore.

247
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:08,667
It's okay to cry, Jas.

248
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:11,033
Just not too much.

249
00:16:11,167 --> 00:16:12,900
Stress is bad for your body,
right?

250
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:15,867
So little by little...

251
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,933
just relax, okay?

252
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,533
I'm tired, Ash.

253
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,767
I just want this to end.

254
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:28,067
I just want to get better.

255
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,000
You will.

256
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:32,233
You're going to be okay.

257
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:34,100
Don't lose hope.

258
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:36,067
Just keep fighting, all right?

259
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,533
So many of us are
rooting for you.

260
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,867
Even Xander.

261
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:46,600
Did you know he visited
while you were gone?

262
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:50,000
He kept asking how you were.

263
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:51,200
Really?

264
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:52,633
What did he say?

265
00:16:52,767 --> 00:16:54,067
What did he do?

266
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,200
Did you guys talk?

267
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:57,833
Yes, cuz.

268
00:16:57,967 --> 00:17:00,200
He was really worried about you.

269
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:04,100
Turns out he's not
a total bad boy.

270
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:06,200
He's actually nice to talk to.

271
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,633
Good listener, too.

272
00:17:08,933 --> 00:17:10,300
And caring...

273
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:12,933
especially toward you.

274
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:16,467
Wow.

275
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:18,200
I was only gone in Hong Kong,

276
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:20,100
and suddenly the wind
had changed.

277
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,500
Weren't you the one who didn't
like him before?

278
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:31,233
I'm not on team bad boy
or team good boy.

279
00:17:31,367 --> 00:17:34,067
I'm on team
Jas-deserves-happiness.

280
00:17:37,667 --> 00:17:44,100
So if Xander is what makes
you happy, I'll support it.

281
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:51,333
Let go of me!

282
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:54,100
What are you doing? Let go!

283
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:55,367
Let go!

284
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,600
After you let your whole
family gang up on me,

285
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:01,200
now you want to talk in private?

286
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:02,467
Don't make this about me!

287
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,000
Why not?

288
00:18:04,133 --> 00:18:07,567
Ever since you opposed
Jasmine's treatment,

289
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:10,567
isn't that exactly
how you made me feel?

290
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:13,067
And you know why I opposed it!

291
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:19,000
Do you think anyone here
feels worse than I do?

292
00:18:19,133 --> 00:18:20,867
No one, Paolo.

293
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,200
No one is angrier at me
than I am at myself.

294
00:18:24,367 --> 00:18:27,600
Because our daughter's
treatment didn't work!

295
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,433
Yeah, you're right.

296
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:32,100
You should be mad at yourself.

297
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:38,400
You only exhausted Jasmine
because of what you did.

298
00:18:38,533 --> 00:18:40,733
You weakened her body even more.

299
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:41,800
For what?

300
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:46,067
So you could say you did
something as a mother?

301
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,533
How dare you!

302
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,900
How dare you!

303
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:51,500
How dare you say that to me

304
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:54,133
after everything
I've been through

305
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:57,100
since Jasmine was a baby!

306
00:18:57,267 --> 00:19:00,200
That's always what you say,
right?

307
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,867
That you're the only one
who struggled raising her.

308
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,667
That I never helped.

309
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,500
That you're the only one
who has the right to our child.

310
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:09,567
That you're the only one
who understands her!

311
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:12,033
For what, huh?

312
00:19:12,167 --> 00:19:14,367
The truth is,

313
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,667
you're the one making our
daughter's condition worse.

314
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:24,100
It's like you're the one
killing her.

315
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:26,667
Just like how you killed
our relationship!

316
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:39,867
I made all those decisions

317
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,733
because I love our daughter
so much.

318
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:46,033
Paolo, I was desperate
to save our child!

319
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:49,400
So don't you ever say I did
all this to Jasmine

320
00:19:49,533 --> 00:19:50,800
because I'm careless!

321
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:52,100
What about you?

322
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:54,433
You always want things your way!

323
00:19:54,567 --> 00:19:56,400
You only care about what
you think is important

324
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:58,367
instead of listening to
what she actually needs!

325
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:00,000
That's not true!

326
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:02,200
Really?

327
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:04,900
Can you control
Jasmine's condition?

328
00:20:05,033 --> 00:20:08,800
Can you control the exact time
she needs her medicine?

329
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:12,200
Can you comfort her
when she cries in pain?

330
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,967
Can you calm her breathing

331
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:16,833
when she wakes up scared
in the middle of the night?

332
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,100
You can't!

333
00:20:18,233 --> 00:20:20,367
Because you're not there!

334
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:22,800
You shouldn't have fought
with Marj like that.

335
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:25,167
So you're really defending Marj?

336
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,733
Edward, I'm your wife.

337
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:29,667
You should be taking my side.

338
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,233
You know what
she's going through.

339
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,000
Their child is sick.

340
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:35,467
She doesn't need more
stress from you people.

341
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:38,367
Marj disrespected your family!

342
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,467
And you're just okay with that?

343
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:41,400
Then again...

344
00:20:41,533 --> 00:20:43,667
you can't even stand up for me.

345
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:46,033
What more your own family?

346
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:51,033
No wonder you're such a loser
in this family!

347
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:53,300
You shut up!

348
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:56,367
While our daughter is suffering,
you're busy with meetings.

349
00:20:56,500 --> 00:21:00,167
With your damn responsibilities
at Torrecampo Realty!

350
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:03,633
The same company that's keeping
her alive!

351
00:21:03,767 --> 00:21:06,067
All her medicine,
all her hospital bills!

352
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,733
Every single thing she needs

353
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:13,633
comes from that company
you hate so much!

354
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:19,533
Don't act like you're the only
one sacrificing here, Marj!

355
00:21:19,667 --> 00:21:23,300
Don't paint me as the villain
in your story!

356
00:21:23,433 --> 00:21:25,900
You were the one who shut me off
in the first place!

357
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:29,800
You make decisions on your own!

358
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:33,567
You never listen to me!

359
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:34,700
You decide everything,

360
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:37,300
but never include me
as your husband.

361
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,967
As Jasmine's father!

362
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:46,600
This has nothing to do
with my family or me.

363
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:48,567
This is about how you acted
earlier!

364
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:49,500
Go ahead!

365
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,600
Go on, hurt me!

366
00:21:51,733 --> 00:21:56,333
Just because of Marj,
you're really going to hurt me?

367
00:21:56,467 --> 00:21:58,000
Go ahead.

368
00:21:58,133 --> 00:21:59,333
Do it!

369
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:01,333
Hit me!

370
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:05,900
So I can finally think
that I married the wrong man!

371
00:22:13,533 --> 00:22:14,967
Yes, you became a mother.

372
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:18,700
But you failed as a wife.

373
00:22:21,567 --> 00:22:23,300
So yes, I blame you.

374
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:29,867
Because while Jasmine's health
keeps getting worse,

375
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,400
our relationship is slowly
falling apart

376
00:22:32,533 --> 00:22:34,600
because of everything
you've done.

377
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:16,167
Marj, have some tea first.

378
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,700
It's a little hot,
but it'll help calm you down.

379
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,667
I'm so exhausted, Manang.

380
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:27,733
I try to stay strong...

381
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:31,900
but sometimes I don't even know

382
00:23:32,033 --> 00:23:33,633
if I'm still doing
the right thing.

383
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:40,867
You know, sometimes
we make decisions

384
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,600
when we're already desperate.

385
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:47,833
Especially when we feel like
we don't have any other choice.

386
00:23:49,733 --> 00:23:54,367
I made a huge mistake myself
once.

387
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:58,833
I trusted something I thought
would solve my problem.

388
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,200
But it didn't.

389
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:04,267
I just ended up
hoping for nothing.

390
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,933
So now...

391
00:24:06,067 --> 00:24:11,200
the only thing I can do
is get back up and move forward.

392
00:24:12,967 --> 00:24:14,700
So, Ma'am...

393
00:24:14,833 --> 00:24:16,400
I hope you can do the same.

394
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:21,300
Jasmine gets her strength
from you.

395
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:23,867
From you and Sir Paolo.

396
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,667
When the two of you are
not getting along,

397
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,467
it becomes even harder
for your daughter

398
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,533
to keep fighting every day.

399
00:24:30,567 --> 00:24:31,633
So I hope...

400
00:24:32,333 --> 00:24:34,567
I really hope you and your
husband can make peace.

401
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:53,033
<i>Don't paint me as the villain
in your story!</i>

402
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:57,467
<i>You were the one who shut me off
in the first place!</i>

403
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,167
<i>You make decisions on your own!</i>

404
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:00,767
<i> You never listen to me!</i>

405
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:01,867
<i> You decide everything,</i>

406
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,900
<i>but you never include me
as your husband.</i>

407
00:25:05,067 --> 00:25:06,767
<i> As Jasmine's father!</i>

408
00:25:07,933 --> 00:25:10,600
<i>Jasmine gets her strength
from you.</i>

409
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:12,400
<i> From you and Sir Paolo.</i>

410
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:14,767
<i>When the two of you are
not getting along,</i>

411
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:16,500
<i>it'll be even harder
for your daughter</i>

412
00:25:16,633 --> 00:25:18,667
<i> to keep fighting every day.</i>

413
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:19,800
<i> So I hope...</i>

414
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:22,100
<i>I hope you and your husband
can make peace.</i>

415
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:27,167
Pao?

416
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:30,267
Love.

417
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,733
Let's not talk right now.

418
00:25:37,033 --> 00:25:38,433
What are you doing?

419
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:40,800
Love?

420
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:44,533
I'll sleep in the guest room
for now.

421
00:25:47,867 --> 00:25:48,800
What?

422
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:52,100
Please, can we talk, Paolo?

423
00:25:53,867 --> 00:25:55,100
I can't talk right now.

424
00:25:55,233 --> 00:25:56,267
Love...

425
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,333
Love.

426
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:44,567
What's this for?

427
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:45,933
Why are you giving me money?

428
00:26:46,067 --> 00:26:49,067
I want you to be my eyes
and ears in this house.

429
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,267
Spy on Marj.

430
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,533
I want to know her every move.

431
00:26:52,667 --> 00:26:53,567
And do everything you can

432
00:26:53,700 --> 00:26:55,467
to make sure she and Paolo
never reconcile.

433
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,333
You know what's funny?

434
00:26:57,467 --> 00:26:59,833
They can't even fix
their own family.

435
00:26:59,967 --> 00:27:01,133
How are they supposed
to run a company?

436
00:27:01,267 --> 00:27:02,333
Shut your foul mouth!

437
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,467
Paolo!

438
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:09,333
Paolo, I know you're
going through a lot.

439
00:27:09,467 --> 00:27:11,900
You don't have to face
everything alone.

440
00:27:12,033 --> 00:27:13,633
I'm here.

441
00:27:13,767 --> 00:27:14,833
At least you're here for me.
